  "text": "The new multi-core architecture will force radical changes in software design and development. We are already seeing significant increase of research interests in concurrency and parallelism, and multi-core software development. The number of multiprocessor research papers has increased sharply since year 2001, surpassing the peak point in all the past years [CITATION_1] . Concurrency is one of the next big challenges in how we write software simply because our industry has been driven by requirements to write ever larger systems that solve ever more complicated problems and exploit the ever greater computing and storage resources that are available [CITATION_2] .",
